{"parse":{"title":"Pointing and calling","pageid":20416105,"revid":860536414,"text":{"*":"<div class=\"mw-parser-output\"><div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Train_Driver_in_Japan_Pointing.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0a/Train_Driver_in_Japan_Pointing.jpg/220px-Train_Driver_in_Japan_Pointing.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"165\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0a/Train_Driver_in_Japan_Pointing.jpg/330px-Train_Driver_in_Japan_Pointing.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/0/0a/Train_Driver_in_Japan_Pointing.jpg/440px-Train_Driver_in_Japan_Pointing.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"3072\" data-file-height=\"2304\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Train_Driver_in_Japan_Pointing.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Train driver pointing</div></div></div>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Organs_involved_during_Pointing_and_Calling.jpg\" class=\"image\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f3/Organs_involved_during_Pointing_and_Calling.jpg/220px-Organs_involved_during_Pointing_and_Calling.jpg\" width=\"220\" height=\"165\" class=\"thumbimage\" srcset=\"//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f3/Organs_involved_during_Pointing_and_Calling.jpg/330px-Organs_involved_during_Pointing_and_Calling.jpg 1.5x, //upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f3/Organs_involved_during_Pointing_and_Calling.jpg/440px-Organs_involved_during_Pointing_and_Calling.jpg 2x\" data-file-width=\"1600\" data-file-height=\"1200\" /></a>  <div class=\"thumbcaption\"><div class=\"magnify\"><a href=\"/wiki/File:Organs_involved_during_Pointing_and_Calling.jpg\" class=\"internal\" title=\"Enlarge\"></a></div>Pointing and calling requires co-action and co-reaction among the operator's brain, eyes, hands, mouth, and ears.</div></div></div>\n<p><b>Pointing and calling</b> is a method in <a href=\"/wiki/Occupational_safety\" class=\"mw-redirect\" title=\"Occupational safety\">occupational safety</a> for avoiding mistakes by pointing at important indicators and calling out the status. It is common in <a href=\"/wiki/Japan\" title=\"Japan\">Japan</a> and railways of <a href=\"/wiki/Taiwan\" title=\"Taiwan\">Taiwan</a>, it is also sometimes referred to by its Japanese terms, <i>shisa kanko</i> (<span lang=\"ja\" title=\"Japanese language text\">\u6307\u5dee\u559a\u547c</span>), <i>shisa kakunin kanko</i> (<span lang=\"ja\" title=\"Japanese language text\">\u6307\u5dee\u78ba\u8a8d\u559a\u547c</span>) or <i>yubisashi kosh\u014d</i> (<span lang=\"ja\" title=\"Japanese language text\">\u6307\u5dee\u547c\u79f0</span>). Making large gestures and speaking out the status helps keeping focus and <a href=\"/wiki/Attention\" title=\"Attention\">attention</a>. The method was first used by train drivers and is now commonly used in Japanese industry. It is not common in other countries, though it is used in the <a href=\"/wiki/New_York_City_Subway\" title=\"New York City Subway\">New York City Subway</a> system. It is recommended by the <a href=\"/w/index.php?title=Japan_Industrial_Safety_and_Health_Association&amp;action=edit&amp;redlink=1\" class=\"new\" title=\"Japan Industrial Safety and Health Association (page does not exist)\">Japan Industrial Safety and Health Association</a> (JISHA, <span lang=\"ja\" title=\"Japanese language text\">\u4e2d\u592e\u52b4\u50cd\u707d\u5bb3\u9632\u6b62\u5354\u4f1a</span>).<sup id=\"cite_ref-japantimes_1-0\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-japantimes-1\">&#91;1&#93;</a></sup><sup id=\"cite_ref-2\" class=\"reference\"><a href=\"#cite_note-2\">&#91;2&#93;</a></sup>\n</p>\n<div class=\"thumb tright\"><div class=\"thumbinner\" style=\"width:222px;\"><div id=\"mwe_player_0\" class=\"PopUpMediaTrans